          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Barbados</placeName>
                                        <date>23 Nov. 1848</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">My Dear Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">I have this instant heard that there is<lb/> a
                                        conveyance for <placeName>Baltimore</placeName>, and embrace
                                        the opportunity<lb/> reluctantly to inform you that the set
                                        of Parasah Books<lb/> you sent me in the early part of last
                                        year, I had sold<lb/> to the <persName>Revd. John
                                                  Birchannon</persName><add>?</add> of the
                                                  <add>?</add> of Barbie with<lb/> a promise that
                                        the amount would be remitted me shortly<lb/> after his
                                        arrival, but <del>but</del> by the last steamer, I
                                        received<lb/> a letter announcing his death, and that all
                                        his property had<lb/> been levied on by excusion to pay a
                                        prior claim against him, con-<lb/>-sequently the amount he
                                        is indebted to me is lost, as he<lb/> has nothing else
                                        available to pay, however on my arrival<lb/> please God, I
                                        hope we shall be able to understand each other,<lb/> as it
                                        is not likely we'll fight about such a trifle as
                                        fifteen<lb/> dollars—please present my family's line to my
                                        sister, <persName>Mr.<lb/> Fontes</persName> and the
                                                  <persName>Carvalhos</persName>, and say my wife is
                                        busily em-<lb/>-ployed cutting out flannels, and other warm
                                        clothing in<lb/> readiness for our departure, and as I have
                                        to attend in pur-<lb/>-chasing the different articles, I
                                        have no time to write<lb/> either of them, hoping that on my
                                        arrival please God<lb/> a mutual good understanding will
                                        exist between us, and<lb/> that it may be in our power to
                                        assist each other.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">I remain</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">My Dear Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">Your's faithfully</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">
                                        <persName role="author">Samuel E. Daniels</persName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>371 Walnut Street</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p>Via <placeName>Baltimore</placeName></p>
